710482f-b.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, north from W. 18th Street (extreme left and not seen), showing structures occupying the 19th-20th Street frontage. At the left is a vacant lot on the easterly half of the 18th-19th Street block and across which appears buildings on the north aide of W. 19th Street. The gap shown there was caused by the demolition in 1930 of a 3 story tenement, No. 507-9 W. 19th Street. View No. 2 is a closer view of this N.W. corner of the Avenue and W. 19th Street and shows in addition the renovation of the adjoining
structure to the aforementioned gap.
July 28, 1931
View 2: July 18, 1932.
P.L. Sperr
